fcmd [INITIAL-QUERY]

Fuzzy-pick any zsh alias, function, builtin, reserved word, or
command on $PATH, with a help preview in the right-hand pane. Names
starting with `_` (completion functions, internal helpers) are
hidden.

Preview priority (first match wins):

  1. $HELPDIR/<name>      — zsh builtin help text file
  2. shell-internal       — alias expansion + function body, captured
                             from the running shell
  3. man <name>           — man page (piped through `col -bx` to
                             strip terminal escapes)
  4. type <name>          — fallback, shows what the name resolves to

On selection the chosen name is pushed onto the next command line
via `print -z`, so you can edit and run it.

The optional INITIAL-QUERY pre-populates fzf's search box.

Requires: fzf.
